In this article, President Trump and General Kelly address the false reporting about their relationship. They both express that they have a great relationship and that General Kelly is doing a fantastic job as Chief of Staff. They also discuss the positive state of the economy, the potential breakthrough in North Korea, and the successful efforts to combat the opioid crisis. President Trump dismisses questions about Stormy Daniels and emphasizes the need to focus on the country's accomplishments and the ongoing witch hunt against him. He also mentions the recent 4 percent growth in the economy and his desire to eventually withdraw troops from South Korea.